          <num>12-241a</num>
          <heading>Definition</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 12-241a. Definition.As used in section12-241, “Connecticut motor bus company” means any common carrier motor bus company, organized in this state and engaged in the business of carrying passengers for hire, to which a certificate has been issued under the provisions of section13b-80and seventy-five per cent of whose gross operating revenue in each calendar year is derived from operations within the state.
